cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with image processing and computer vision, specifically the problem of single image de-raining. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses conditional generative adversarial networks (GANs) for optimization, which falls under the category of machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also introduces a new loss function, which involves discriminative performance, indicating that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with image quality and visual performance, which may fall under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
